title: Anderson is quizzed by psychologist on if he's 'languishing'
description: Psychologist Adam Grant runs through a series of questions with Anderson Cooper to see if Anderson is "languishing". Watch "Full Circle" Monday, Wednesday and Friday at 6p E.T.

title: 'Is everything I'm trying to do pointless?': Syrians helpless in face of 'sham' election
description: Syrians are voting in presidential elections widely dismissed by experts and activists as a sham poll, rigged in favor of President Bashar al-Assad. CNN's Jomana Karadsheh reports.

title: China's incredible high-speed rail network
description: At the beginning of the 21st century China had no high-speed railways.

title: What it's like to walk 220 miles above Earth
description: Former NASA Astronaut Danny Olivas describes what it's like to perform a spacewalk and explains why astronauts do them.

title: The biggest open-air 'prison' on Earth?
description: Despite the US announcement to provide immediate disaster assistance to Gaza, the future for many civilians living in Gaza -- which has been under an Israeli-Egyptian blockade since 2007 -- is bleak with little chance to step foot outside the area. CNN's Ben Wedeman reports.

title: Brother of journalist detained in Myanmar says family is hopeful
description: An American journalist working in Myanmar was detained by local authorities, his family and his news organization told CNN. CNN's John Vause speaks to his brother Bryan Fenster.

title: Stunning aerial photos capture synchronized swimmers from above
description: The scene is viewed from above: Eight women in white halter bathing suits and matching swim caps form geometric shapes in a pristine turquoise swimming pool. They cascade like dominoes on the diagonal, join their arms and legs in kaleidoscopic compositions, and peek out from under the white shimmery discs of open parasols.
